							<h1 class="h2 text-center">Everpower Upgrading Guide
							</h1>
							<br>
							<h6 class="mt-0 mb-1 text-center">
								<small class="text-muted">Author: Adrian
								</small></h6>
							<h6 class="mt-0 mb-1 text-center">
								<small class="text-muted">Last updated: 2/13/2019
								</small></h6>
							<br>
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="card-body mx-auto">
									<ul class="list-unstyled">
										<li class="media my-4">
											<img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="/images/everpower/augustus.png" style="height: 500px;">
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Introduction</h5>
												<p>
													Okay, so you've got your Level 175 Gear and now it's time to upgrade it!
													But wait - there's this whole new Everpower thing and it's super confusing.
													Well, I'm here to show you how easy it really is!
													<br><br>
													First off, we're going to pay a visit to our good friend Augustus. He's the guy to go tofor everything related to Everpower Upgrading.
													You can find Augustus in the left-hand sector of Central Flarine, next to the Crafting NPC.
												</p>
												<p class="text-muted">
													Disclaimer: Because ProtosHeis has added normal awakening to Everpower Gear and changed the way Arcane Slots work, the gifs are not visually up to date but they still teach you what you need to know.
												</p>

											</div>
										</li><!-- End Section-->

										<li class="media my-4 guide-section">
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Refining</h5>
												<p>
													Everyone wants that shiny +20 gear, and we're no different. First things first, you're going to need two different upgrading materials: Shreds of Power and some kind of Everdust.
													<br><br>
													Everdust is available in four tiers:
												</p>
												<ul>
													<li class="guide-tool-tip-link text-primary"><span data-toggle="popover" data-container="body" data-placement="right" data-html="true" href="#" id="everdust"><img class="mx-1" src="/images/Icons/Itm_SysEverdust.png"
															    style="width: 32px; height: 32px;"><strong>Everdust</strong></span></li>
													<div id="popover-content-everdust" class="d-none">
														<h5 class="card-title">Everdust</h5>
														<p class="card-text">Description: A powerful powder that is used to enhance the strength of your gear. Used for enchanting Epic/Legendary gear up to +10.</p>
														<p class="card-text">Obtainable from Hillid Mountains and Icy Caverns.</p>
													</div>
													<li class="guide-tool-tip-link text-primary"><span data-toggle="popover" data-container="body" data-placement="right" data-html="true" href="#" id="arcane-everdust"><img class="mx-1" src="/images/Icons/Itm_SysEverdust.png"
															    style="width: 32px; height: 32px;"><strong>Arcane Everdust</strong></span></li>
													<div id="popover-content-arcane-everdust" class="d-none">
														<h5 class="card-title">Arcane Everdust</h5>
														<p class="card-text">Description: A powerful powder that is used to enhance the strength of your gear. Used for enchanting Epic/Legendary gear from +11 up to +20.</p>
														<p class="card-text">Obtainable from Hillid Mountains and Icy Caverns.</p>
													</div>
													<li class="guide-tool-tip-link text-primary"><span data-toggle="popover" data-container="body" data-placement="right" data-html="true" href="#" id="ethereal-everdust"><img class="mx-1" src="/images/Icons/Itm_SysEtherealEverdust.png"
															    style="width: 32px; height: 32px;"><strong>Ethereal Everdust</strong></span></li>
													<div id="popover-content-ethereal-everdust" class="d-none">
														<h5 class="card-title">Ethereal Everdust</h5>
														<p class="card-text">Description: The chances of succeeding with an enchantment are higher than with normal Everdust. Can be used on any enchantment level.</p>
														<p class="card-text">Obtainable from Loot Boxes only.</p>
													</div>
													<li class="guide-tool-tip-link text-primary"><span data-toggle="popover" data-container="body" data-placement="right" data-html="true" id="divine-everdust"><img class="mx-1" src="/images/Icons/Itm_SysDivineEverdust.png"
															    style="width: 32px; height: 32px;"><strong>Divine Everdust</strong></span></li>
													<div id="popover-content-divine-everdust" class="d-none">
														<h5 class="card-title">Divine Everdust</h5>
														<p class="card-text">Description: The chances of succeeding with an enchantment are highest with this Everdust. Can be used on any enchantment level.</p>
														<p class="card-text">Obtainable from Cash Shop only.</p>
													</div>
												</ul>
												<br>
												<p>To refine your item, simply drag and drop it into the middle slot of the Everpower Enchanting window. Add your Everdust and Shreds of Power to the allocated slots on either side, and hit 'START'.
													<br>
													There is a chance that your upgrade will fail at ANY refinement level (even +0) but your item will NEVER break. If the upgrade fails, simply hit 'RESET' and try again.
												</p>
											</div>
											<img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="/images/everpower/refining.gif" style="height: 500px;">
										</li><!-- End Section-->

										<li class="media my-4 guide-section">
											<img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="/images/everpower/everpowering.gif" style="height: 500px;">
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Everpowering</h5>
												<p>
													Everpowering is the process required t get your item from +10 to +11 so you may continue refining with Everdust. To do this, we're going to need Everpower Scrolls.
													<br><br>
													Once your Everpower Scroll is slotted into the Enchanting Window, just follow the same process as Refining and hit 'START'.
													<br><br>
													Once your item reaches +11, its time to start refining again. You'll need to use Arcane Everdust from +11 to +20 or Ethereal/Divine Everdust to increase your success rate.
												</p>
											</div>
										</li>
										<li class="media my-4 guide-section">
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Awakening</h5>
												<p>
												Awakening with the Everpower system is very simple!
												<br>
												The number of awakening lines a weapon has is dtermined by two things: rarity and refinement level.
												<br><br>
												Epic (Corpsemaker) Equipment has 3 lines at max - unlocked at +6, +14, and +20.
												<br><br>
												Legendary (Soulreaver) Equipment has 4 lines at max - unlocked at +6, +12, +16, and +20.
												<br><br>
												Once your piece of equipment has been upgraded far enough to have an Awakening line, simply double-click on a Power Serum and then click on your weapon/armor piece, just as you would with a normal awakening scroll.
												<br><br>
												Unlike normal awakening, there is no need for a Scroll of Reversion! If you're not happy with the awakening you have recieved, just repeat the process over again to reroll instantly.
												</p>
												<p>
													<strong>IMPORTANT</strong>
													<br>
													As of the PvP Casualization v2.6.0 Update, you can now use normal awakening scrolls on Level 175 Gear as well in addition to Everpower Awakening.
												</p>
											</div>
											<img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="/images/everpower/awakening.gif" style="height: 500px;">
										</li> <!-- End Section -->

										<li class="media my-4 guide-section">
											<!-- <img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="https://www.kronaflyff.com/Content/Public/News/15020413030d907b2422934953.jpg" style="width: 400px; height: 240px;" alt="News"> -->
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Everpower Awakening Values</h5>
												<p>
													Critical Chance and Casting Time: 1%/2%/4%
													<br>
													STR/DEX/INT/STA: 4/8/15
													<br>
													Critical Damage: 3%/6%/10%
													<br>
													Physical and Magical Defense: 100/150/250
													<br>
													Physical and Magical Attack: 80/160/300
													<br>
													Healing: 5%/7.50%/10%
													<br>
													Max. HP: 420/840/1600
													<br>
													Max. MP: 100/150/250
													<br>
													Speed: 1%/2%/3%
													<br><br>
													(per individual line)
												</p>
												<p>
													Be warned: all Everpower Awakening lines will reroll at the same time whenever you use a Power Serum. So if you have one or more lines you would really like to keep, continue on to the Powerbinding section below to find out how.
												</p>

											</div>
										</li><!-- End Section-->

										<li class="media my-4 guide-section">
											<!-- <img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="https://www.kronaflyff.com/Content/Public/News/15020413030d907b2422934953.jpg" style="width: 400px; height: 240px;" alt="News"> -->
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Superior Scroll of Awakening Values</h5>
												<p>
													Critical Chance and Casting Time: 1%/2%/3%/4%/5%/6%/7%/8%/9%
													<br>
													STR/DEX/INT/STA: 2/6/11/15/20/24/29/33/38/42
													<br>
													Critical Damage: 2%/4%/7%/10%/13%/16%/19%/22%/25%
													<br>
													Physical and Magical Defense: 50/100/150/200/250/300/350/400/450
													<br>
													Physical and Magical Attack: 240/330/420/510/600/690/780/870/960
													<br>
													Healing: 1%/2%/3%/4%/5%/8%/9%
													<br>
													Max. HP: 320/680/1040/1400/1720/2080/2440/2800/3120
													<br>
													Max. MP: 50/100/150/200/250/300/350/400/450
													<br>
													Speed: 1%/2%/3%/4%/5%/7%/8%/9%
													<br><br>
													(per individual line)
													<br>
												</p>
												<p>
													Be warned: all Awakening lines will reroll at the same time whenever you use a Superior Scroll of Awakening.
												</p>

											</div>
										</li><!-- End Section-->

										<li class="media my-4">
											<img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="/images/everpower/powerbinding.gif" style="height: 500px;">
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Powerbinding</h5>
												<p>
													Powerbinding is a process which allows you to continue Awakening your item while preserving the lines you wish to keep!
													<br><br>
													Three things are required to use the Powerbinding system: A level 175 Weapon/Armor piece with an existing awakening, Power Serum, and Powerbinds.
													<br><br>
													To use the Powerbinding interface, put your item into the leftmost slot, and then add you power serum and Powerbinds in the allocated slots.
													<br><br>
													Any box that you <strong>CHECK</strong> will have its Awakening line saved, and any box that you leave <strong>UNCHECKED</strong> will be rerolled.
													<br><br>
													Once you have selected the boxes corresponding to the lines you wish to keep, simply hit 'AWAKEN'. All of the lines left <strong>UNCHECKED</strong> will nw be rerolled.
													<br><br>
													Please make <strong>absolutely sure</strong> that you check the correct boxes, otherwise you will lose your awakening line!
												</p>
											</div>
										</li><!-- End Section-->

										<li class="media my-4">
											<div class="media-body mr-3">
												<h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">Arcane Slots</h5>
												<p>
													Arcane Slotting is another powerful way to get useful Stats onto your equipment.
													<br><br>
													Arcane slots are only available on Weapons.
													<br><br>
													Weapons come with a single Arcane Slot, and additional slots will unlock as you refine to +20 for a maxmium of 5 Arcane Slots.
													<br><br>
													To unlock your Weapon's Arcane potential, simply double click on a Dragon Stone and click to apply to your Weapon.
													<br><br>
													If you're unhappy with the results, click on Augustus and go to the Arcane Slots Setup window. Drag your Weapon and Reverse Enigma Codex into the allocated slots, select the Dragon Stone you wish to remove and hit 'REMOVE'. Use another Dragon Stone on your weapon to try again.
												</p>
											</div>
											<img class="d-none d-sm-block mr-3" src="/images/everpower/arcane-slot.gif" style="height: 500px;">
										</li><!-- End Section-->

									</ul>
								</div>

							</div>
						</div>
